<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 08 at 2:38AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Beaver
and northeastern Texas Counties through 315 AM CDT...
At 238 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hooker, or 16 miles southwest of Liberal, moving southeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hooker, Tyrone, Bryans Corner, Baker, Adams, Boyd, Turpin and Floris.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Oklahoma.</instruction>
